About this hotel

Off a rural road, this regal hotel on lush grounds is 10 km from the 19th-century Bahia Palace and 16 km from Marrakesh Menara Airport.

    I have to start my review by thanking the staff of Palais Ronsard for what was an unforgettable stay. From the moment I was greeted at the door I felt welcome. The place is absolutely beautiful with no attention to detail spared. The rooms 
    I have to start my review by thanking the staff of Palais Ronsard for what was an unforgettable stay. From the moment I was greeted at the door I felt welcome. The place is absolutely beautiful with no attention to detail spared. The rooms were oversized, the ceilings high, and they are decorated beautifully. The grounds were impeccably maintained and every one of the staff members was friendly. I was traveling alone and looking for some peace and quiet. They have a no children policy which was perfect with me and the other guests seemed to be on the same page. I understand that some people may not like that but there are many of us that enjoy the peace and quiet of no children when we vacation. This is a perfect couples location. The food was delicious and the menu was creative. The Matre De Maison, the Chef and even the Owner took the time to introduce themselves and spent a lot of time visiting and getting to know me and make sure that I was enjoying my stay. If you are visiting Marrakesh, even if only for one night, treat yourself to Palais Ronsard. You can thank me for the recommendation later. Thank you everyone at Palais Ronsard. A true 5 star experience. I will be back!

    Annakhil

    The sprawling suburb of Annakhil includes golf courses and palm groves, with paths and horse-carriage tours through 100,000 trees at El Palmeral. Inside that park is Muse de la Palmeraie, showing a century of Moroccan paintings in a 1940s colonial farmhouse. MACAAL is a more modern space, displaying pan-African art. Residential areas have casual tagine restaurants, while resort hotels have chic bars and bistros.

    About this hotel

    Off a rural road, this regal hotel on lush grounds is 10 km from the 19th-century Bahia Palace and 16 km from Marrakesh Menara Airport.

    Featuring coffered ceilings and marble bathrooms, the airy, plush suites offer terraces, fireplaces and sitting areas. Villas add private plunge pools. All provide satellite TV, free Wi-Fi, minibars and Nespresso machines. Some have claw-foot tubs.

    Amenities include an outdoor pool, 2 restaurants, 2 bars and a garden. Theres also a spa with a sauna, a hammam and a fitness center. Breakfast and an airport shuttle are available (fee). Children age 12 and over are welcome.
